⚙️ Methodology
1. Object Detection
Model: YOLOv8
Detects surgical tools in each video frame
Outputs bounding boxes, confidence scores, and class labels
2. Object Tracking
Uses built-in tracking (model.track())
Assigns unique IDs to tools
Maintains temporal consistency across frames
3. Danger Zone Definition
A polygon region representing a critical area
Defined manually using coordinates
Can be static or configurable
danger_zone = np.array([[x1,y1], [x2,y2], [x3,y3], [x4,y4]])
4. Distance Estimation
Computes distance between tool center and danger zone
Uses geometric function:
cv2.pointPolygonTest()
Output:
Positive → inside zone
Negative → outside zone
Magnitude → distance
5. Alert Mechanism
Threshold-based risk classification:
Safe
Warning
Critical
Temporal smoothing applied to avoid flickering:
if distance < threshold:
    warning_count += 1
6. Visualization
Bounding boxes around tools
Danger zone overlay (polygon)
Real-time warning text:
cv2.putText(frame, "WARNING!", ...)
